/*
 * Magic Menu
 */
app:magic-menu
  name:Magic Menu 7.0
  description:A common menu system and speech input system for all your P5 apps
  price:Free
  local-url:magic-menu
  image:"https://phosphorusfive.files.wordpress.com/2017/11/odtssey2001_16.jpg"
  developer-key:5E11AEF421CDB0A7A9A5C6B4AED9D04F43BE2AAD
  url:"https://phosphorusfive.files.wordpress.com/2018/01/magic-menu.zip"
  condition:p5.io.unroll-path.@MAGIC
  version:decimal:7.0
    event:magic-menu.version
  author-readme:@"Magic Menu is a bridge between natural spoken language and computer code, allowing you to evaluate Hyperlambda, as a response to natural language, by speaking phrases and words, in your own language if you wish - Or chosing menu items.

There are really no words in existence to accurately describe this. However, this is one of those things you simply have to see in action to believe in. Notice, speech recognition only works in Google Chrome.

It supports most common languages on the planet, and can literally do anything. It basically allows your Phosphorus Five installation to understand human language, and translate it into computer code, almost automatically for you."





