  version:decimal:7.0
    event:sulphur.version
  author-readme:@"Sulphur Five is a secure file sharing system, built with your privacy in mind.

Sulphur Five allows you to share files privately with only yourself, and protected which means with any registered user in your system, or publicly which means the world at large.

Sulphur Five also has many other interesting attributes, such as the ability to describe your files using Markdown, and #hash_tagging your files."





/*
 * Peeples
 */
app:peeples
  name:Peeples 7.0
  description:A user management module for Phosphorus Five. Allows you to create, edit and delete users
  url:"https://phosphorusfive.files.wordpress.com/2018/01/peeples.zip"
  price:Free
  local-url:peeples
  image:"https://phosphorusfive.files.wordpress.com/2017/08/users.png"
  developer-key:5E11AEF421CDB0A7A9A5C6B4AED9D04F43BE2AAD
  condition:p5.io.unroll-path.@PEEPLES
  version:decimal:7.0
    event:peeples.version
  author-readme:@"Peeples is the user management module for Phosphorus Five, that allows you to create, edit and delete users in your installation.

This is the module you need if you want to create additional user accounts in your Phosphorus Five installation.

In addition, it allows you to administrate your access objects, to grant or deny access to some specific part of your system, according to the roles of your users."





